obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31959)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31959&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Reciprocity Act, 1943.`
  line
  line `(2) it extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) It shall come into force on the 1st day of September, 1943.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except Part B States" omitted by s. 3 and the Sch., ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1943, s. 2, for the original sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31960)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31960&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "British Possession" means any part of His Majesty's dominions ^2*** and includes a`
  line `protectorate or other territory administered by a British Possession as a mandatory on behalf of the`
  line `League of Nations; and where parts of those dominions are under both a central and a local`
  line `legislature, the expression shall mean either each part under a local legislature or all parts under the`
  line `central legislature;]`
  line
  line `(b) "entry" includes landing at any port in ^3[India] during the stay in ^3[India] of a ship or aircraft`
  line `on its way to a destination outside ^3[India] :`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for the original cl. (a).`
  line
  line `2. The words "exclusive of India" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch., for "the States".`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (c) ins. by the A.O. 1950, omitted by s. 3 and the Sch. ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31961)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to impose reciprocal disabilities on persons domiciled in British Possessions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31961&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Power of Central Government to impose reciprocal disabilities on persons domiciled in`
  line `British Possessions.--Where by the law or practice of any British Possession persons of Indian origin are`
  line `subject in that British Possession to disabilities in respect of entry into, or travel, residence, the`
  line `acquisition, holding or disposal of property, the enjoyment of educational facilities, the holding of public`
  line `office, the carrying on of any occupation, trade, business or profession, or the exercise of the franchise in,`
  line `that British Possession, to which in respect of the like matters in ^2[India] persons domiciled in that British`
  line `British Possession are not subject in ^2[India], the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that the same disabilities or disabilities as similar thereto as may be shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, be imposed in ^2[India] on persons not`
  line `being of Indian origin who- are domiciled in that British Possession.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1943, s. 4, for the original s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for "the States".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31962)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Burden of proof on person claiming exemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31962&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `If any person alleged to be domiciled in any`
  line `British Possession and to be subject to the provisions of this Act pleads that he is not so domiciled, or that`
  line `the provisions of this Act do not apply to him, the onus of proving the truth of such a plea shall be on him.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31963)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Direction imposing disabilities in respect of entry, travel and residence not to apply to armed forces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31963&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^2[5. Direction imposing disabilities in respect of entry, travel and residence not to apply to`
  line `armed forces.--Any direction made by the Central Government under section 3 imposing disabilities in`
  line `respect of entry into or travel or residence in ^1[India] upon persons domiciled in a British Possession shall`
  line `not, until the expiry of six months after the termination of the present hostilities, apply to any person`
  line `domiciled in that British Possession who is a member of its armed forces.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 1943, s. 5, for the original s. 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31964)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31964&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^2[6. Power to make rules. --(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under this`
  line `section may provide --`
  line
  line `(a) for the setting up of machinery to ascertain the disabilities in respect of any of the matters`
  line `specified in section 3 to which persons of Indian origin are subject in any British Possession;`
  line
  line `(b) for the establishment of a suitable agency to administer the rules and for defining its functions`
  line `and powers;`
  line
  line `(c) for specifying the disabilities that shall, when a direction has been made under section 3, be`
  line `imposed in ^1[India] on persons not being of Indian origin who are domiciled in any British Possession`
  line `and for the imposition on them of the disabilities so specified;`
  line
  line `(d) for the enforcement, by the prescription of a penalty by way of imprisonment or fine or both,`
  line `or any rule made under clause (c);`
  line
  line `(e) for authorizing the arrest of any person contravening or reasonably suspected of contravening`
  line `any rule made under clause (c), and for prescribing the duties of public servants and others in regard`
  line `to such arrests.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Sch. for "the States".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for the original s. 6.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 the Sch. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31965)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Repealed.
  content `^1[7. Repeal of Act 3 of 1924.--The Immigration into India Act, 1924, is hereby repealed.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 1943, s. 7.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604&sectionId=31965&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_0_00019_194309_1523353991604
